title: Jonah From Tonga Season 1
description:
Jonah from Tonga is an Australian television comedy series written by and starring comedian Chris Lilley. The mockumentary series follows Jonah Takalua, a rebellious 14-year-old boy of Tongan descent who was previously seen in Lilley's series Summer Heights High. 
 In this series his father, Rocky Takalua, has sent him back to his homeland of Tonga to live with his uncle and their family in order to get Jonah's life back on track
 The entire series will be available for streaming online for one weekend from 2 May to 4 May on BBC iPlayer & ABC iview, before starting a six-week run on ABC1 on 7 May 2014 and from 8 May on BBC Three. This is a first for a major Australian TV production
